title: Carroll boys, girls sweep cross country regionals
text:
Carroll boys, girls sweep cross country regionals 
By Dean Pantazi - 21 Alive October 17, 2015 Updated Oct 17, 2015 at 11:31 PM EDT 
LIGONIER, Ind. (21 Alive) - Carroll rolled to wins Saturday in both cross country regionals at West Noble. 
The boys won with points, and will be joined by the other fourth top five team finishers, Concordia, Westview, West Noble, and Snider, at the semi-state at the Plex next week.

Homestead's Brayden Law was over 30 seconds clear of the rest of the field in winning individually in 15:17.81. 
The Carroll girls won their record 15th straight regional by putting all five of their runners in the top 14 to finish with 42 points. 
They will be joined by Homestead, East Noble, DeKalb, and Dwenger at semi-state. 
Maridson Fruchey of Carroll won individually in 18:04.95.
